docs.lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Oregon, April 26.--A collision occurred last night in the Willamette River, a few miles below Portland, between the British steamship Danube and the American steamship Alliance. The Danube was bound for this city from Victoria, and the Alliance was bound down the river.

docs.lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA, April 24.--Human endurance put an end to Capt. Hamilton Murrell's round of pleasure this afternoon, and the 1,400 orphan boys who had arrayed themselves in the chapel of Girard College to pay their respects to him suffered a disappointment. This morning the Captain was entertained at lunch at the Stock Exchange by the Board of Brokers, and met, among many others, A.J. Drexel and George W. Childs.
